In[6]:
#Filtro banda
def bandpass(data, fs, low, high, order=4):
    b, a = butter(order, [low/(fs/2), high/(fs/2)], btype='band')
    return filtfilt(b, a, data, axis=1)
In[7]:
#Coherencia

def compute_coherence_matrix(data, fs, fmin, fmax, nperseg=None):
    n_channels = data.shape[0]
    nperseg = nperseg or int(fs*2)
    coh = np.zeros((n_channels, n_channels))

    for i in range(n_channels):
        for j in range(i, n_channels):
            f, Cxy = coherence(data[i], data[j], fs=fs, nperseg=nperseg)
            mask = (f >= fmin) & (f <= fmax)
            val = np.mean(Cxy[mask]) if mask.any() else np.mean(Cxy)
            coh[i, j] = val
            coh[j, i] = val

    np.fill_diagonal(coh, 0)
    return coh
In[8]:
#PLV
def compute_plv_matrix(data):
    analytic = hilbert(data, axis=1)
    phases = np.angle(analytic)
    n_channels = phases.shape[0]
    plv = np.zeros((n_channels, n_channels))

    for i in range(n_channels):
        for j in range(i+1, n_channels):
            phase_diff = phases[i] - phases[j]
            val = np.abs(np.mean(np.exp(1j*phase_diff)))
            plv[i,j] = val
            plv[j,i] = val

    np.fill_diagonal(plv, 0)
    return plv
In[9]:
#Threshold
def threshold_matrix(mat, percentile=75):
    vals = mat.flatten()
    vals = vals[~np.isnan(vals)]
    th = np.percentile(vals, percentile)

    mat_bin = (mat >= th).astype(int)
    mat_thresh = mat.copy()
    mat_thresh[mat < th] = 0

    return mat_thresh, mat_bin, float(th)
In[10]:
#Filtro poblacional
def population_filter(binary_matrices, pop_pct=0.5):
    arr = np.stack(binary_matrices, axis=2)
    frac = arr.mean(axis=2)
    keep = (frac >= pop_pct).astype(int)
    return keep

#Mtricas del grafo
def graph_metrics_from_adj(adj):
    G = nx.from_numpy_array(adj)
    deg = dict(G.degree(weight='weight'))
    betw = nx.betweenness_centrality(G)
    clust = nx.clustering(G, weight='weight') if len(G) > 0 else {}

    try:
        comms = list(community.greedy_modularity_communities(G))
        modularity = nx.community.modularity(G, comms) if comms else None
    except Exception:
        comms = []
        modularity = None

    return {
        "graph": G,
        "degree": deg,
        "betweenness": betw,
        "clustering": clust,
        "communities": comms,
        "modularity": modularity
    }

# Heatmaps
def plot_heatmap(mat, ch_names, title, outpath, annotate=False):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6,5))
    df = pd.DataFrame(mat, index=ch_names, columns=ch_names)
    ax = plt.gca()
    im = ax.imshow(df.values, aspect='equal')
    plt.colorbar(im, ax=ax, fraction=0.046)

    if annotate:
        for (i,j), val in np.ndenumerate(df.values):
            ax.text(j, i, f"{val:.2f}", ha='center', va='center', fontsize=6)

    ax.set_xticks(range(len(ch_names)))
    ax.set_xticklabels(ch_names, rotation=90, fontsize=6)
    ax.set_yticks(range(len(ch_names)))
    ax.set_yticklabels(ch_names, fontsize=6)

    plt.title(title)
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.savefig(outpath, dpi=150)
    plt.close()
In[13]:
#Grafo 2D
def plot_graph_2d(G, ch_names, pos=None, title=None, outpath=None, node_size_map=None):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6,6))

    if pos is None:
        pos = nx.spring_layout(G, seed=RANDOM_SEED)

    node_sizes = [node_size_map.get(i, 100) if node_size_map else 100 for i in range(len(G.nodes()))]

    nx.draw(G, pos, with_labels=True,
            labels={i: ch_names[i] for i in range(len(ch_names))},
            node_size=node_sizes)

    if title: plt.title(title)
    if outpath: plt.savefig(outpath, dpi=150)
    plt.close()

#Grafo 3D
def plot_graph_3d(G, ch_names, title, outpath, node_size_map=None):
    from mpl_toolkits.mplot3d import Axes3D

    fig = plt.figure(figsize=(6,6))
    ax = fig.add_subplot(111, projection='3d')

    pos3d = {}
    n = len(ch_names)

    for i, ch in enumerate(ch_names):
        angle = 2*np.pi*(i/n)
        x, y, z = np.cos(angle), np.sin(angle), 0
        pos3d[i] = (x,y,z)
        size = node_size_map.get(i, 50) if node_size_map else 50
        ax.scatter(x, y, z, s=size)
        ax.text(x, y, z, ch, fontsize=8)

    for u,v,data in G.edges(data=True):
        ax.plot([pos3d[u][0], pos3d[v][0]],
                [pos3d[u][1], pos3d[v][1]],
                [pos3d[u][2], pos3d[v][2]], alpha=0.6)

    ax.set_title(title)
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.savefig(outpath, dpi=150)
    plt.close()

# Procesador
def process_ensemble(df_group, group_id, outroot, fs=256.0, method="plv",
                     band_key="alpha", threshold_percentile=75):

    ch_names = CHANNELS
    data = df_group[ch_names].to_numpy(dtype=float).T
    n_channels, n_samples = data.shape
    ensure_dir(outroot)

    fmin, fmax = BANDS[band_key]

    # 1) Filtro banda
    data_bp = bandpass(data, fs, fmin, fmax)

    # 2) Conectividad
    if method == "coherence":
        conn = compute_coherence_matrix(data_bp, fs, fmin, fmax)
    elif method == "plv":
        conn = compute_plv_matrix(data_bp)
    else:
        raise ValueError("method must be 'coherence' or 'plv'")

    # 3) Guardar conectividad continua
    plot_heatmap(conn, ch_names,
                 f"Connectivity ({method}) {band_key} - {group_id}",
                 os.path.join(outroot, "heatmap_continuous.png"))
    pd.DataFrame(conn, index=ch_names, columns=ch_names)\
        .to_csv(os.path.join(outroot, "adjacency_continuous.csv"))

    # 4) Threshold
    conn_thresh, conn_bin, th = threshold_matrix(conn, percentile=threshold_percentile)

    plot_heatmap(conn_thresh, ch_names,
                 f"Thresholded >= {th:.3f} ({threshold_percentile}p)",
                 os.path.join(outroot, "heatmap_thresholded.png"))
    
    plot_heatmap(conn_bin, ch_names,
                 f"Binary adjacency ({threshold_percentile}p)",
                 os.path.join(outroot, "heatmap_binary.png"))

    pd.DataFrame(conn_thresh, index=ch_names, columns=ch_names)\
        .to_csv(os.path.join(outroot, "adjacency_thresholded.csv"))

    # 5) Grafos y mtricas
    metrics = graph_metrics_from_adj(conn_thresh)
    G = metrics["graph"]
    degree = metrics["degree"]

    node_size_map = {i: (degree.get(i,0)+1)*80 for i in range(len(ch_names))}

    plot_graph_2d(G, ch_names, title=f"Graph 2D - {group_id}",
                  outpath=os.path.join(outroot, "graph2d.png"),
                  node_size_map=node_size_map)

    plot_graph_3d(G, ch_names, title=f"Graph 3D - {group_id}",
                  outpath=os.path.join(outroot, "graph3d.png"),
                  node_size_map=node_size_map)

    # Resumen JSON
    comms = metrics["communities"]
    betw = metrics["betweenness"]
    top_hub = max(betw.items(), key=lambda x: x[1]) if betw else (None, None)

    metrics_out = {
        "group_id": str(group_id),
        "method": method,
        "band": band_key,
        "threshold_percentile": float(threshold_percentile),
        "threshold_value": float(th),
        "num_nodes": int(n_channels),
        "num_edges": int(G.number_of_edges()),
        "degree": {ch_names[k]: float(v) for k,v in degree.items()},
        "betweenness": {ch_names[k]: float(v) for k,v in betw.items()},
        "clustering": {ch_names[k]: float(v) for k,v in metrics["clustering"].items()},
        "modularity": float(metrics["modularity"]) if metrics["modularity"] is not None else None,
        "communities": [[ch_names[n] for n in sorted(list(c))] for c in comms ],
        "top_hub": (ch_names[top_hub[0]], float(top_hub[1])) if top_hub[0] is not None else None
    }

    with open(os.path.join(outroot, "metrics.json"), "w") as f:
        json.dump(metrics_out, f, indent=2)

    return conn_thresh, conn_bin, metrics_out

#filtrado poblacional de conectividad
def run_pipeline_on_csv(data_path, out_root, fs, method, band, thresh_pct, pop_filter_pct=None):
    df = pd.read_csv(data_path)

    # Validacin de columnas
    missing = [c for c in CHANNELS + ['ID'] if c not in df.columns]
    if missing:
        raise ValueError(f"Faltan columnas esperadas en el CSV: {missing}")

    ensure_dir(out_root)

    summary = []
    binary_matrices = []
    ids = df['ID'].unique()
    print(f"Se encontraron {len(ids)} ID(s). Procesando cada ID...")

    for gid in ids:
        df_g = df[df['ID'] == gid].reset_index(drop=True)
        outdir = os.path.join(out_root, str(gid))
        ensure_dir(outdir)

        print(f"Procesando ID = {gid} -> muestras: {len(df_g)}")

        conn_thresh, conn_bin, metrics = process_ensemble(
            df_g, gid, outdir, fs=fs, method=method,
            band_key=band, threshold_percentile=thresh_pct
        )

        summary.append(metrics)
        binary_matrices.append(conn_bin)

    # Filtro poblacional
    if pop_filter_pct is not None:
        print("Aplicando filtro poblacional:", pop_filter_pct)
        pop_keep = population_filter(binary_matrices, pop_pct=pop_filter_pct)

        pd.DataFrame(pop_keep, index=CHANNELS, columns=CHANNELS)\
            .to_csv(os.path.join(out_root, "population_filtered_edges.csv"))

        Gpop = nx.from_numpy_array(pop_keep)
        nx.write_gml(Gpop, os.path.join(out_root, "population_graph.gml"))

    summary_df = pd.json_normalize(summary)
    summary_df.to_csv(os.path.join(out_root, "summary_metrics.csv"), index=False)

    print("Pipeline completado. Resultados en:", out_root)

#Umbral grupal
def threshold_percentile(mat, p=75):
    th = np.percentile(mat.flatten(), p)
    bin_mat = (mat >= th).astype(int)
    mat_thr = mat.copy()
    mat_thr[mat < th] = 0
    return mat_thr, bin_mat, th

group_thr = {}
group_bin = {}
thresholds = {}

for group in group_avg:
    thr, bin_m, th = threshold_percentile(group_avg[group], p=75)
    group_thr[group] = thr
    group_bin[group] = bin_m
    thresholds[group] = th

#Funcin para graficar grafo grupal
def plot_group_graph(group_name, adj_matrix):
    G = nx.from_numpy_array(adj_matrix)

    degree = dict(G.degree(weight="weight"))
    betw = nx.betweenness_centrality(G)

    hub_index = max(betw, key=betw.get)
    hub_name = CHANNELS[hub_index]
    hub_value = betw[hub_index]

    colors = ["red" if i == hub_index else "skyblue" for i in range(len(CHANNELS))]
    sizes = [900 if i == hub_index else 300 + degree.get(i,0)*40 for i in range(len(CHANNELS))]

    pos = nx.spring_layout(G, seed=42)

    plt.figure(figsize=(8,8))
    nx.draw_networkx(G, pos, node_color=colors, node_size=sizes, font_size=8)
    plt.title(f"Grafo Grupal  {group_name}\nHub: {hub_name} (betw={hub_value:.3f})")
    plt.axis("off")
    plt.show()

    return hub_name, hub_value

#Grafo 3D
def plot_group_graph_3d(adj_matrix, group_name):
    G = nx.from_numpy_array(adj_matrix)

    degree = dict(G.degree(weight="weight"))
    betw = nx.betweenness_centrality(G)

    hub_index = max(betw, key=betw.get)
    hub_name = CHANNELS[hub_index]
    hub_val = betw[hub_index]

    n = len(CHANNELS)
    pos3d = {i: (np.cos(2*np.pi*i/n), np.sin(2*np.pi*i/n), 0) for i in range(n)}

    node_colors = ["red" if i == hub_index else "skyblue" for i in range(n)]
    node_sizes = [200 if i == hub_index else 50 + degree.get(i, 0)*10 for i in range(n)]

    fig = plt.figure(figsize=(8,7))
    ax = fig.add_subplot(111, projection='3d')

    for i, (x, y, z) in pos3d.items():
        ax.scatter(x, y, z, s=node_sizes[i], c=node_colors[i])
        ax.text(x, y, z, CHANNELS[i], fontsize=8)

    for u, v in G.edges():
        x = [pos3d[u][0], pos3d[v][0]]
        y = [pos3d[u][1], pos3d[v][1]]
        z = [pos3d[u][2], pos3d[v][2]]
        ax.plot(x, y, z, alpha=0.4)

    ax.set_title(f"Grafo 3D  {group_name}\nHub: {hub_name} (betw={hub_val:.3f})")

#Comunidades
from networkx.algorithms.community import greedy_modularity_communities

def compute_communities(adj_matrix):
    """Calcula comunidades y modularidad."""
    G = nx.from_numpy_array(adj_matrix)
    comms = list(greedy_modularity_communities(G))
    modularity = nx.algorithms.community.modularity(G, comms)
    return G, comms, modularity
In[38]:
#color por comunidad
def get_color_map(G, comms):
    """Asigna un color entero a cada nodo segn su comunidad."""
    color_map = {}
    for idx, com in enumerate(comms):
        for node in com:
            color_map[node] = idx
    return [color_map[node] for node in G.nodes()]

# Grafo 2D con comunidades
def plot_communities_2d(G, comms, group_name):
    """Grafica comunidades en 2D."""
    colors = get_color_map(G, comms)
    cmap = cm.get_cmap("tab10", len(comms))
    pos = nx.spring_layout(G, seed=42)

    plt.figure(figsize=(8,7))
    nx.draw_networkx_edges(G, pos, alpha=0.4)
    nx.draw_networkx_nodes(G, pos, node_color=colors, cmap=cmap, node_size=400)
    nx.draw_networkx_labels(G, pos, labels={i: CHANNELS[i] for i in G.nodes()}, font_size=8)

    plt.title(f"Comunidades 2D  {group_name}\nTotal: {len(comms)}")
    plt.axis("off")
    plt.show()

#Grafo 3D con comunidades
def plot_communities_3d(G, comms, group_name):
    """Grafica comunidades en 3D."""
    colors = get_color_map(G, comms)
    cmap = cm.get_cmap("tab10", len(comms))

    n = len(G.nodes())
    pos3d = {i: (np.cos(2*np.pi*i/n), np.sin(2*np.pi*i/n), 0) for i in G.nodes()}

    fig = plt.figure(figsize=(8,7))
    ax = fig.add_subplot(111, projection='3d')

    for node in G.nodes():
        x, y, z = pos3d[node]
        ax.scatter(x, y, z, s=120, c=[cmap(colors[node])])
        ax.text(x, y, z, CHANNELS[node], fontsize=8)

    for u, v in G.edges():
        ax.plot([pos3d[u][0], pos3d[v][0]],
                [pos3d[u][1], pos3d[v][1]],
                [pos3d[u][2], pos3d[v][2]],
                alpha=0.3)

    ax.set_title(f"Comunidades 3D  {group_name}\nTotal: {len(comms)}")
    plt.show()
